# .beads/issues.jsonl is a passive export regenerated by beads on every write.
# The real issue data lives in the Dolt DB and syncs over refs/dolt/data
# (`bd dolt push` / `bd dolt pull`) — see .beads/README.md. Letting git
# three-way-merge the export produces conflicts on nearly every rebase while
# resolving nothing, so keep our side and let beads' post-merge hook rewrite
# it from the database.
#
# Requires merge.ours.driver, set in config/git/config.
.beads/issues.jsonl merge=ours

# Same reasoning: the interaction log is append-only machine output.
.beads/interactions.jsonl merge=ours
